cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with the problem of multilingual ontology matching, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and database technologies. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of SPARQL requests to access Wiktionary data, which falls under the scope of cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper involves comparing the results obtained using Wiktionary with those based on Google Translate API, which could be considered as a machine learning task and thus falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the Semantic Web, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
